To compile this Pokertimer you will need:
* sbcl (to run the compiler)
* gcc  (to compile the resulting binary)

It was tested on:
* Mac OS X Leopard Intel (works)
* Debian Linux (32bit)   (works)
* Ubuntu Linux (64bit)   (works)

To compile and run Pokertimer example:
- Goto the toplevel elco directory
- execute
  # examples/run_pokertimer.sh

If you have ideas or questions go to: http://elco.sourceforge.net

Have fun! :)
